MIT is testing a hydrogel-based panel that can pull water directly from the air with zero power, basically a real-life Star Wars moisture farm. Linus and Luke geek out over the tech, its potential to supply drinking water in emergencies, and of course, how much moisture Uncle Owen was really farming on Tatooine.

Nintendo has been granted a patent that essentially covers summoning another character to battle on your behalf, something that sounds a lot like Pokémon battles or classic RPG mechanics. Linus and Luke break down why this kind of patent could be problematic for the industry, how it differs from trademarks, and whether there’s any universe where this could benefit consumers.

Linus and Luke react to Intel’s bizarre decision to launch what’s essentially a 10th-gen chip from 2020 as if it were brand new. The specs are identical down to the socket and feature list, raising questions about deceptive branding and whether Intel is just dumping old stock in disguise.
